This is the NICOS 2 instrument control system
=============================================

Starting points
---------------

Start a basic system and experiment:

  $ bin/nicos-demo

Documentation: for release packages look in doc/build/html.


Installing
----------

To install, you need to select or create a customization in custom/.

If that exists, use

  make install

and/or

  make install-gui


Requirements
------------

* At least Python 2.6
  - python-devel (headers and static library) (xbuntu 12.04: python-dev)

* numpy (xbuntu 12.04: python-numpy)

* Optional for the basic system:
  - the TACO Python libraries
  - scipy (for fitting) (xbuntu 12.04: python-scipy)
  - MySQLdb (for proposal DB query) (xbuntu 12.04: python-mysqldb)
  - python-xmpp (for Jabber notifications (xbuntu 12.04: python-pyxmpp)
  - pyserial (for TACO-less serial line communication) (xbuntu 12.04: python-serial)
  - matplotlib (for resolution plots) (xbuntu 12.04: python-matplotlib)
  - gnuplot-py (for liveplot display) (xbuntu 12.04: python-gnuplot)
  - gnuplot (for plots in the electronig logbook) (xbuntu 12.04: gnuplot)
  - Grace (for scanplot) (xbuntu 12.04: grace)
  - lxml (for U-Bahn service) (xbuntu 12.04: python-lxml)
  - pyfits (for the handling of FITS formatted files) (xbuntu 12.04 python-pyfits)
  - sphinx (for generating doc) (xbuntu 12.04 python-sphinx)

* For the GUI and status monitor:
  - PyQt4 (xbuntu 12.04: python-qt4 for developers: python-qt4-dev)
  - numpy (xbuntu 12.04: python-numpy)
  - PyQwt (optional, for plots) (xbuntu 12.04: python-qwt5-qt4 python-sip-dev)
  - scipy (optional, for fitting) (xbuntu 12.04: python-scipy)

* Under Windows:
  - pyreadline (optional, for the console to work)
  - colorama (optional, for colored console output)

* To run the test suite:
  - nose (xbuntu 12.04: python-nose)
  - coverage (optional) (xbuntu 12.04: python-coverage)
